    <text id="F8037T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Rankin writes Cameron about local party politics.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>Franklin Repository and Transcript<lb/>Terms $2. Per Annum In Advance<lb/>Five
                    Copies $9. Ten Copies $15.<lb/>Circulation 3,500. 
                    <name type="recipient">A. N. Rankin<lb/><abbr expan="September">Sep.</abbr> 16,/<abbr expan="1856">56</abbr></name>     
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1856-09-16"><abbr expan="September">Sep.</abbr> 16 1856</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Pa.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Simon">S.</abbr> Cameron<lb/>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have been so much engaged since receiving your's that I could not till now find
                    time to answer. I very well remember meeting with you in Harrisburg, but
                    supposed you had entirely forgotten me.</p>
                <p>I have been twice around<pb n="2"/>the County, once to secure the nomination of
                    one of my partners, for this office of State Senator. And once to secure the
                    right person to fill a vacancy that occurred in our Assembly Ticket.</p>
                <p>In both instances I was successful.</p>
                <p>Our county the Birthplace of Buchanan is truly the battle-ground<pb n="3"/>we
                    will have to fight for every inch of ground we get.</p>
                <p>I Love the American Party and especially the Democratic portion of it. I joined
                    the order from the Democracy. We have gained between 2 and 5 hundred of that
                    kind of votes and lost about 200 Catholic &amp; Foreign votes.</p>
                <p>I will be in Harrisburg the last of this or the first of next week.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Truly Your Friend</salute>
                    <signed>A. N. Rankin</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
